<TITLE> Zhang wins China another gold in Weightlifting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BEIJING, Aug 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Zhang Xiangxiang secured China's second Olympic weightlifting gold of the day on Monday in the men's 62kg class after almost half of the contenders dropped out following three failed attempts. The 25-year-old snatched 143kg and lifted 176kg for the clean and jerk. He took gold with a total of 319kg. Colombian Diego Salazar took silver and Indonesian Triyatno, who only goes by one name, the bronze, in a contest that was full of unexpected twists and turns. Several medal hopefuls tried to dramatically raise their weights in a bid for the podium, only to see their risky strategy crash when they failed to execute the lift. That left space for Salazar, who had not been among the favourites for the contest, to stage his surprise assault for a medal. Fired on by chants of "Colombia! Colombia!" from flag-waving Colombian fans in yellow T-shirts, he upped his game in the clean and jerk. In the women's 58kg competition earlier in the day, Chen Yanqing won gold for China, becoming the first woman to win two Olympic weightlifting gold medal
